Zimbabwe Lawyers for Truth, Health, Justice and Freedom and two other rights organisations have filed papers in the Harare High Court. They say children can’t give consent and want them removed from the mass vaccination programme. They say government has backtracked on its promise that vaccinations will be voluntary. eNCA correspondent Pindai Dube reports. #DStv403 HARARE - Zimbabwe rights NGOs are dragging government to court. They are demanding it to stop COVID-19 vaccination for adolescents. Last month, children between 12 and 17 were added to the mass vaccination programme. READ: Zimbabwe considers banning unvaccinated from public transport Zimbabwe Lawyers for Truth, Health, Justice and Freedom and two other rights organisations have filed papers in the Harare High Court They say children can’t give consent and want them removed from the mass vaccination programme. They say government has backtracked on its promise that vaccinations will be voluntary. * eNCA correspondent Pindai Dube reports.